  "prompt": "Why isn\u2019t Pok\u00e9mon GO working?",
  "response": "If Pok\u00e9mon GO isn't working, there could be several reasons behind the issue. Here are some common causes and possible troubleshooting steps:\n\n1. **Server Issues:** The game might be experiencing temporary server problems. Check Pok\u00e9mon GO's official social media accounts or community forums to see if other players are facing similar issues.\n\n2. **Internet Connection:** Make sure you have a stable internet connection. Try switching between Wi-Fi and mobile data to see if that resolves the issue.\n\n3. **App Updates:** Ensure that you have the latest version of the Pok\u00e9mon GO app installed. Visit the app store on your device to check for any available updates.\n\n4. **Device Compatibility:** Check if your device meets the minimum requirements to run Pok\u00e9mon GO. Sometimes older devices or operating systems may no longer be supported.\n\n5. **Location Services:** Pok\u00e9mon GO relies on GPS data. Ensure that location services are enabled for the app. You can check this in your device\u2019s settings.\n\n6. **Cache and Data:** Try clearing the cache and data of the Pok\u00e9mon GO app. This can be done through your device settings, under the app management section.\n\n7. **App Permissions:** Verify that Pok\u00e9mon GO has all the necessary permissions enabled, such as access to your location, storage, and camera.\n\n8. **Reinstall the App:** If none of the above steps work, try uninstalling and reinstalling the Pok\u00e9mon GO app. This can sometimes resolve persistent issues.\n\n9. **Device Restart:** Sometimes simply restarting your device can resolve temporary software glitches.\n\n10. **Contact Support:** If the issue persists, you may need to contact Niantic's support team for further assistance. You can do this through the Pok\u00e9mon GO website or app.\n\nBy following these troubleshooting steps, you might be able to identify and resolve the issue causing Pok\u00e9mon GO to not work properly.",
